        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-05-22 05:54:47.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> With this change start.sh script will not be able to be used in standalone mode. Can you create another script to do this?\n\nOk. What is the use case to run plugin like the start.sh did? I.e. what is the standalone mode? \nstart.sh started plugin locally build (not docker) go modules from that dir and left application to foreground. Seems like very development type of usage and not usable on any imaginary deployment use case?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
